<input type="hidden" name="link" value="s289"><input type="hidden" name="return" value="http://www.darkflame.org/data.cgi?mode=DF;uline=;snum=289"><input type="hidden" name="mode" value="DF"><input type="submit" name=".submit" value="Post Comment" /></form><BR>
<TABLE CLASS="SPELLS" WIDTH=100%>
<TR><TH>Negate Harmful Effects<BR>
<I><FONT SIZE=-1>Posted 1999-12-10 21:19:56 by Solarstorm</FONT></I></TH></TR>
<TR><TD>This spell is useful in that you can negate harmful effects cast on you by NPCs. The most effective use is to cast all &quot;buffs&quot; (at least two low-cost mana spells) on the PC (i.e. strengthen and minor shielding), next use Taper Enchantement on PC so that first (top) effect slot is open.   In this way if a monster (i.e. putrid skeleton) casts a spell on the PC (i.e. weaken) all you have to do is cast Taper enchantment to negate that monster's spell and your &quot;buffs&quot; shall remain.  NOTE that Tamper Enchantment only works on the first spell effect slot (top) so if the slot is not available when the NPC casts on you, the caster would have to continue to negate all spell effects until reaching the NPC-generated effect.  This spell also works well for removing the effects of Charms. </TD></TR>
</TABLE>

